a) Aim to reduce electricity consumption in the Company restaurants;
b) Increase the coverage of employees for: skill development training, and health & safety training;
c) Aim to reduce plastic footprint in Company restaurants;
d) Aim to strengthen governance, business ethics and integrity and code of conduct through continuous training of employees for POSH, Code of Conduct, Whistle Blower and Prohibition of Insider Training; and
e) Maintain robust compliance and integrity practices.

During the year, the Company has:
a) Trials for monitoring electricity unit consumption by different equipments are regularly conducted to identify opportunities to optimize electricity unit consumption and the Company undertakes various electricity cost saving initiatives like light load reduction, etc.;
b) All restaurant employees have access to online learning management systems for skill development training and health & safety training;
c) Glasses for dine-in guests are re-used for about 9 months in the restaurants. Glasses served to delivery guests can be re-used by them. Other products which contain plastic are not reused. They are either recycled through EPR program or safely disposed at restaurants through local municipality waste collection;
d) Business Ethics and Integrity and Code of Conduct: Annual Mandatory training for all employees has been introduced by the Company for POSH, Code of Conduct, Whistle-blower & Prohibition of Insider Trading on Company’s shares and year-on-year trainings are conducted for the same; and
e) Use of Compliance Management Tool for tracking compliances.

